Title:
Crimes against NTDLL ‚Äì Implementing Early Cascade Injection (Rust)

Type:
Blog Post

Short Summary (4‚Äì8 sentences max):
- This post explains how to implement Outflank‚Äôs ‚ÄúEarly Cascade Injection‚Äù technique in Rust to execute code at the earliest stage of Windows user-mode process initialization.  
- It abuses NTDLL‚Äôs Application Compatibility Shim Engine by enabling `g_ShimsEnabled` and redirecting the shim DLL-load callback pointer (`g_pfnSE_DllLoaded` / `g_fnSE_DllLoaded`) to attacker-controlled code.  
- The target process is created suspended, stage-1 bootstrap code is injected, and the shim callback pointer is patched (with required pointer encoding) so execution occurs during normal loader activity (around `LdrInitializeThunk`).  
- The stage-1 stub (written as `no_std` Rust ‚Äúshellcode-like‚Äù code) disables shims immediately and queues a same-thread APC via `NtQueueApcThread` to run a stage-2 payload (e.g., reflective DLL loader).  
- It avoids common injection artifacts like `CreateRemoteThread`, cross-process APC injection, and thread context hijacking, and can run before many user-mode EDR hooks/telemetry components initialize.  
- The write-up also covers resolving undocumented NTDLL globals via byte-pattern scanning and handling encoded callback pointers using `SharedUserData!Cookie` at `0x7FFE0330`.  
- Useful for red teamers/implant developers building stealthy spawn-and-inject primitives; also relevant to defenders studying early-process injection and loader/shim abuse.

Technical Focus:
- NTDLL loader internals (`LdrInitializeThunk`) and early user-mode execution
- Application Compatibility Shim Engine abuse (`g_ShimsEnabled`, `g_pfnSE_DllLoaded`)
- Pointer encoding/decoding using `SharedUserData!Cookie` (system pointer encoding)
- Byte-pattern scanning to locate undocumented globals in NTDLL
- `no_std` Rust stubs as position-independent bootstrap code
- Same-thread APC execution via `NtQueueApcThread` / dispatch via `NtTestAlert`

Use Cases:
- Stealthy spawn-and-inject for C2 implants prior to user-mode EDR initialization
- Fileless payload execution without remote thread creation
- Building early-stage loaders that transition into reflective DLL injection
- Researching/detecting shim-engine variable tampering and early loader callback abuse

Keywords:
